history.content: Anecdotally, I've heard that the compilers class has gotten easier than before (haven't taken it myself).

children.subject:
I took CS 164 (compilers) and CS 194-15 (parallel programming) together last semester. It was a very manageable courseload, although it might've helped that I had a great team for 164. I can't compare this class to previous offerings so I don't know how much easier it's gotten but I thought it was comparable to CS 162 with Kubiatowicz. 194-15 was really chill, probably because it was the first time the class was offered so the assignments weren't as fully developed. We had weekly-ish labs, 1-2 week homeworks, and 4 quizzes (with a quiz drop, I believe). Overall, I think most students did really well in this class, and it was (imo) easier than Data 100 when I took it. 

I'd recommend either this combo or 162 + 194-15 (maybe the latter because operating systems is interesting -- and generally more applicable -- and you're graduating so that might be a higher priority than compilers!).

history.content:

I was wondering if both 162 and the compilers class are very high workload?
If I was to take one of 162/compilers and one of the special topics, which 2 would you recommend based on workload?
Most importantly, which of these 4 is the lowest workload?
